: BrightBlade panted as she came up beside Perndabot, resting her hands on 
her knees and bowing her head, trying to catch her breath.
She had never run that fast in her whole entire life, and she hoped to the 
Pit that she wouldn�t have to do that again.
Imagine, more then three months in Maximal custody, how depressing. Some 
infiltrator she had turned out to be.
And what information she had gathered was now useless, and the Predacon ship 
didn�t even register on her scanners anymore.
What she knew was enough to make her cringe anyway; the Predacons were being 
lead by far too many new commanders now, and even Hell Beast served instead 
of led now. So, was there any place left for her in the Predacon forces? She 
doubted it.
But for now it was time to rest.
BrightBlade breathed deeply, finding her spark beat calming down a bit so 
that she could actually stand straight.
She looked back along with Perndabot at the Cybertronian Fire, still 
wondering just how the heck they could have made it out of that hell hole 
alive.
BrightBlade nodded at Perndabots words.:
